===Etymology===
; “multitudinous; vast; ocean”:
: {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} compares it with {{cog|bo|ཡངས་པ||wide; extensive; vast; spacious}}. In contrast, {{zh-ref|Starostin}} sets up {{cog|sit-pro||*lɨ̆ŋ|wave}}, encompassing this and {{cog|bo|ཀློང||space; expanse; wave}}, {{cog|my|လှိုင်း||wave; to abound; plentiful}}.
: Compare {{och-l|羕|(''of rivers'') long}}, {{och-l|漾|waves; (''of rivers'') long}}.
; "vast expanse of flat land"
: The same word as {{och-l|陽}}, which is a variant of {{och-l|野|id=1|plain}}, used in {{zh-l|平陽|flat land}} and many place names in which {{zh-l|陽}} does not seem to mean "south side of mountain or north side of river" ({{zh-ref|Pan, 2016}}). It is also the same word as {{zh-l|垟}}, used in place names. Cognate with {{zh-l|浪}}, {{zh-l|塱}}, {{zh-l|埌}} used in place names.

